Emu Run

by: grace04

This game was made for my level 2 project at The League of Amazing Programmers.
Click here to download and play!

1. Why I Made This Game

I made this game as one in the Emu series. I like the Chrome dinosaur game, and this was inspired by that and OverSimplified.

2. What I Learned

I learned that the character wasn't jumping correctly, I also learned that unlimited bullets was too overpowered. This led me to make better jumping mechanics and limit the amount of bullets to 12.

3. Architecture of My Game

EmuRun sets the frame for the game, GamePanel changes the game states, the Human class lets the character jump. ObjectManager spawns enemies, checks for if an object is dead, and allows the player to shoot.

4. Technical Implementation

The human character used to bounce up and down, and wouldn't jump every time the button was pressed. It now uses doubles velocity, power, and gravity, and also the boolean canJump. This fixed the bouncing and made the jumping mechanic very reliable.

5. Most Challenging Part

It was difficult to get the human to jump every time, and that made the game extremely difficult. Players will die not because they didn't press the button, but because the character couldn't move. I overcame this difficulty by modifying the code that controls jumping to include a canJump boolean and a double named power.

6. Future Fixes and Updates

I would add different difficulties or modes, and add different types of obstacles.

7. Why is the game like this?

Because it's Australia.
